    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Once everything is almost ready, combine the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>cornflour</strong> and <strong>soy</strong> <strong>sauce</strong> in a small bowl with your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>curry</strong> <strong>powder </strong>and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> and give everything a good mix up, then put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until thickened, stirring halfway – this is your <strong>curry sauce</strong></p>",
